19 judicial proceedings, proceedings of another, and who receives or is promised
20 consideration for doing so."
21 SECTION 2.(b) G.S. 58-71-41 reads as rewritten:
22 "§ 58-71-41. First-year Provisional licensees; limitations.
23 (a) Except as provided in this section, a first-year provisional licensee shall have the same
24 authority as other persons licensed as bail bondsmen or runners under this Article. Except as
25 provided in subsection (d) of this section, a first-year provisional licensee shall operate only
26 under the direct supervision of and from the official business address of a licensed supervising
27 bail bondsman bondsman, who shall be responsible for the direct supervision of the provisional
28 licensee, for the first 12 24 months of licensure. A first-year provisional licensee may only be
29 employed by or contract with one supervising bail bondsman.
30 (b) When a first-year provisional licensee has completed 12 24 months of supervision,
31 six of which shall be uninterrupted, the supervising bail bondsman shall give notice of that fact
32 to the Commissioner in writing. If the licensee will continue to be employed by or contract with
33 the supervising bail bondsman beyond the initial 12-month 24-month period, the supervising bail
34 bondsman shall continue to supervise and be responsible for the licensee's acts.
35 (c) If the employment of or contract with a first-year provisional licensee is terminated,
36 the supervising bail bondsman shall notify the Commissioner in writing and shall specify the
37 reason for the termination.
38 (d) If, after exercising due diligence, a first-year licensed bail bondsman provisional
39 licensee is unable to become employed by or to contract with a supervising bail bondsman, the
40 first-year licensed bail bondsman provisional licensee must submit to the Department a sworn
41 affidavit stating the relevant facts and circumstances regarding the first-year licensed bail
42 bondman's provisional licensee's inability to become employed by or contract with a supervising
43 bail bondsman. The Department shall review the affidavit and determine whether the first-year
44 licensed bail bondsman provisional licensee will be allowed to operate as an unsupervised bail
45 bondsman. A first-year licensed bail bondsman is prohibited from becoming a supervising bail
46 bondsman during the first two five years of licensure.
47 (e) Provided all other licensing requirements are met, an applicant for a bail bondsman
48 or runner's license who has previously been licensed with the Commissioner for a period of at
49 least 18 consecutive months and who has been inactive or unlicensed for a period of not more
50 than three consecutive years shall not be deemed a new licensee for purposes of this section."
