1 SECTION 2.(c) Article 71 of Chapter 58 of the General Statutes is amended by
2 adding a new section to read:
3 "§ 58-71-41.1. Requirements for supervising bail bondsmen.
4 (a) A bail bondsman who seeks to act as a supervising bail bondsman or to restore a
5 revoked supervising bail bondsman status shall meet all of the following requirements:
6 (1) Submit an application on a form approved by the Commissioner and pay a
7 two hundred dollar ($200.00) application fee.
8 (2) Have five years of uninterrupted experience as a licensed bail bondsman in
9 this State.
10 (3) Have not violated an order of the Commissioner or had adverse administrative
11 action taken against the bail bondsman's license pursuant to G.S. 58-71-80.
12 (4) The bail bondsman shall possess or demonstrate the competence, experience,
13 or integrity considered by the Commissioner to be necessary to serve as a
14 supervising bail bondsman.
15 (b) A supervising bail bondsman shall submit to the Commissioner, on a form prescribed
16 by the Commissioner, both of the following:
17 (1) No later than May 31 of each year, a renewal application on a form prescribed
18 by the Commissioner. Failure to comply with this subdivision shall result in
19 revocation of a bondsman's status as a supervising bail bondsman.
20 (2) No later than the fifth business day of each month, a record of each provisional
21 licensee supervised by the supervising bail bondsman.
22 (c) A supervising bail bondsman shall not:
23 (1) Charge a fee for supervising a provisional licensee.
24 (2) Supervise more than two provisional licensees at one time."
25 SECTION 2.(d) Any bail bondsman (i) acting as or seeking to act as a supervising
26 bail bondsman or (ii) seeking to restore a revoked supervising bail bondsman status shall submit
27 the application and fee required by G.S. 58-71-41.1, as enacted by this act, within 60 days of the
28 effective date of this act.
