30 PART III. CHANGES TO DISCIPLINARY STATUTE TO ALLOW FOR
31 ADMINISTRATIVE ACTION BASED ON THE COMMISSION OF CERTAIN
32 CRIMES; PROVISIONAL LICENSEE CONFORMING CHANGE
33 SECTION 3. G.S. 58-71-80 reads as rewritten:
34 "§ 58-71-80. Grounds for denial, suspension, probation, revocation, or nonrenewal of
35 licenses.
36 (a) The Commissioner may deny, place on probation, suspend, revoke, or refuse to renew
37 any license issued under this Article, in accordance with the provisions of Article 3A of Chapter
38 150B of the General Statutes, for any one or more of the following causes:
39 …
40 (6a) Violation of a statute or ordinance that results in injury or death.
41 …
42 (8a) When, in the judgment of the Commissioner, the licensee has used
43 unnecessary or excessive force in performing the functions, duties, and
44 powers under the license issued by the Commissioner.
45 …
46 (b) The Commissioner shall deny, revoke, or refuse to renew any license under this
47 Article if if (i) the applicant or licensee is or has ever been convicted of a felony.felony or (ii)
48 pursuant to the provisions of Article 3A of Chapter 150 of the General Statutes, the
49 Commissioner, or another appropriate administrative body, finds that the applicant or licensee
50 performed the acts necessary to satisfy the elements of a felony.
51 …
