30 PART V. PHYSICAL LOCATION FOR OFFICIAL BUSINESS ADDRESS
31 SECTION 5. G.S. 58-71-40 reads as rewritten:
32 "§ 58-71-40. Bail bondsmen and runners to be qualified and licensed; license applications
33 generally.
34 (a) No person shall act in the capacity of a professional bondsman, surety bondsman, or
35 runner or perform any of the functions, duties, or powers prescribed for professional bondsmen,
36 surety bondsmen, or runners under this Article unless that person is qualified and licensed under
37 this Article. No licensee shall participate in or solicit assistance in securing custody of a principal
38 by another not licensed under this Article. No license shall be issued under this Article except to
39 an individual natural person.
40 …
41 (f) A licensee shall have an official business address that is a physical location in the
42 State of North Carolina. Official business addresses shall reflect an established office separate
43 and apart from any residence or other business. The address required by this subsection shall be
44 provided to the Commissioner designating where required business records are maintained upon
45 examination pursuant to G.S. 58-71-170. The physical location used as the official business
46 address must comply with all local or municipal zoning ordinances and regulations. Use of a post
47 office box as an official business address is prohibited."
48
